Create a REPOSITORIES direcotry and download CAP and GEOTOOLS inside it. These are private repositories so you will need permisson from Carl Tape (ctape@alaska.edu)

> mkdir ~/REPOSITORIES/

%------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
PREREQUISITE

0. Install cap (https://github.com/uafseismo/capuaf)

> cd ~/REPOSITORIES/
> git clone --depth=1 https://GITHUBUSERNAME@github.com/uafseismo/capuaf.git capuaf
> cd capuaf
> make all

1. Get a copy of GEOTOOLS (https://github.com/uafseismo/GEOTOOLS)
> cd ~/REPOSITORIES/
> git clone --depth=1 https://GITHUBUSERNAME@github.com/uafseismo/GEOTOOLS.git GEOTOOLS

%--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
DATA EXTRACTION and SETUP

2. Extract waveforms from IRIS:
> cd ~/REPOSITORIES/GEOTOOLS/python_util/util_data_syn/

In run_getwaveform.py set "iex = 100" 
> python run_getwaveform.py

This will create the data directory 20090407201255351 inside ~/REPOSITORIES/GEOTOOLS/python_util/util_data_syn/.

3. Copy input weight file into the data directory:
> cp ~/REPOSITORIES/cap/EXAMPLES/20090407201255351_check/weight.dat ~/REPOSITORIES/GEOTOOLS/python_util/util_data_syn/20090407201255351/weight_test.dat

%--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------
RUN CAP

4. Input command
> cap.pl -H0.02 -P1/15/60 -p1 -S2/10/0 -T15/150 -D1/1/0.5 -C0.25/0.6667/0.025/0.0625 -Y1 -Zweight_test.dat -Mscak_39 -m4.5 -I50000 -R0/0 20090407201255351
